- They're going to hit me!

580
00:30:45,120 --> 00:30:46,440
I am not!

581
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,800
Do you even care about the law?

582
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:48,640
We are here,

583
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:49,760
yet you dare throw your weight around.

584
00:30:50,280 --> 00:30:51,280
I...

585
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:53,120
Sirs,

586
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:55,160
this is a family matter.

587
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:56,240
We are not the same family.

588
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:57,560
How is it a family matter?

589
00:30:57,880 --> 00:30:58,640
Today, before all

590
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:00,280
of these heroic officials,

591
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:01,480
don't even think about doing anything.

592
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:02,840
They will surely help me,

593
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:03,280
right?

594
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:04,600
Right.

595
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:05,880
Fine.

596
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:06,800
Just you wait.

597
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:08,160
Let's go.

598
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:09,400
Let's go.

599
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,520
I'll be waiting.

600
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:15,640
Enough. Let's go.

601
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:24,080
I'm here to bring the lady her food.

602
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:56,480
Lian,

603
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:58,160
where are you going?

604
00:31:58,480 --> 00:31:59,720
Did you deliver the food to the lady?

605
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:01,560
I did.

606
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:04,040
Why are you acting weird today?

607
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:07,520
I don't feel well.

608
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:09,480
I would like to take the day off.

609
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:10,360
Take the day off?

610
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:11,760
Raise your head for me.

611
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:18,040
I have been infected
with the recent cold.

612
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:20,320
I'm afraid of infecting you.

613
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:21,880
Alright.

614
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,040
Go back and rest.

615
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:24,480
Don't infect the Master and Miss.

616
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:25,520
Yes.

617
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:29,600
Sir,

618
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,640
the soldiers Master Anzu brought

619
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:33,080
have occupied every city gate.

620
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:34,720
Once His Majesty returns,

621
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,400
we can execute our plan.

622
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:38,240
Once His Majesty is dead,

623
00:32:38,320 --> 00:32:40,440
the throne will be yours.

624
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:42,560
Remember,

625
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,240
we must be very careful this time.

626
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:46,120
Nothing must go wrong.

627
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:46,840
Yes.

628
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:56,600
This is bad.

629
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:58,400
I must tell Huai'an.

630
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:09,960
Why is it you?

631
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:11,960
Where is the lady?

632
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:16,000
Go on.

633
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:18,120
Where are you going?

634
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:19,480
The Master asked me
to buy some vegetables.

635
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:20,160
Where is your token?

636
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:21,040
Over here.

637
00:33:21,200 --> 00:33:21,720
Go on.

638
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:24,680
Where are you going?

639
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,600
My father fell ill.

640
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:29,640
I would like to head home to visit him.

641
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:30,480
Where is your token?

642
00:33:31,860 --> 00:33:32,420
Halt!

643
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:35,000
Let go!

644
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:38,440
Father,

645
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,320
I'm begging you.

646
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:41,720
Please stop!

647
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:44,200
His Majesty and I grew up together.

648
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,960
He is your nephew.

649
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:49,000
How can you do this, Father?

650
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:51,960
Tie her up.

651
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:52,920
Keep a closer eye on her.

652
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:54,600
If she escapes again,

653
00:33:54,600 --> 00:33:55,560
you will all die.

654
00:33:55,560 --> 00:33:56,200
Yes.

655
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,000
Father.

656
00:33:58,440 --> 00:33:59,120
Father.

657
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,280
Father.

658
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:09,800
Why hasn't Steward Lu
and Guard Kong returned yet?

659
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,320
Come in.

660
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,520
The soldiers are all gone.

661
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:23,700
Your Majesty.

662
00:34:29,720 --> 00:34:31,080
Everything is ready.

663
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:32,520
Well?

664
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:35,440
Does this mean we can return?

665
00:34:37,240 --> 00:34:39,160
But how are you going to get back?

666
00:34:39,240 --> 00:34:41,200
The soldiers are
searching all the way out here.

667
00:34:41,200 --> 00:34:43,200
The city guards will be worse.

668
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:47,840
I have a plan.

669
00:34:55,640 --> 00:34:56,600
Why are you looking at me?

670
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:58,840
I've done all I can
by helping you until now.

671
00:34:59,520 --> 00:35:00,440
I'm going back to Ximi.

672
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:30,100
♪When a gust of wind brushes past♪

673
00:35:30,100 --> 00:35:33,660
♪The sand and wind burn with passion♪

674
00:35:33,660 --> 00:35:36,740
♪Unafraid to forego a chance
to quench our thirst♪

675
00:35:36,740 --> 00:35:40,540
♪Like camels walking with eyes closed♪

676
00:35:40,540 --> 00:35:43,660
♪When the rain falls
into a rare silence♪

677
00:35:43,660 --> 00:35:47,380
♪Thinking of hardships
you and I don't know♪

678
00:35:47,380 --> 00:35:50,380
♪No need to hum the wind's song♪

679
00:35:50,380 --> 00:35:54,460
♪Uncaring of the darkening skies♪

680
00:35:54,460 --> 00:35:56,140
♪I understood all that for you♪

681
00:35:56,140 --> 00:35:57,900
♪But you have disappeared♪

682
00:35:57,900 --> 00:35:59,580
♪I am lost in the dark♪

683
00:35:59,580 --> 00:36:01,300
♪How should I stop?♪

684
00:36:01,300 --> 00:36:02,980
♪Loving you feels like another lifetime♪

685
00:36:02,980 --> 00:36:06,660
♪But yearning flows into a poem♪

686
00:36:06,660 --> 00:36:09,620
♪For us to meet again♪

687
00:36:09,620 --> 00:36:12,980
♪Requires the promise of millennia♪

688
00:36:12,980 --> 00:36:15,220
♪Watching the rain hail down♪

689
00:36:15,220 --> 00:36:20,300
♪It's like you're still beside me♪

690
00:36:20,300 --> 00:36:23,260
♪When I want to cross over♪

691
00:36:23,260 --> 00:36:27,340
♪To touch you♪

692
00:36:27,340 --> 00:36:29,780
♪But I can't see your fading face♪

693
00:36:29,780 --> 00:36:34,060
♪On the opposite shore♪

694
00:36:34,060 --> 00:36:37,060
♪How do I voice this?♪

695
00:36:37,060 --> 00:36:40,460
♪My heart beats uneasily♪

696
00:36:40,460 --> 00:36:43,380
♪How I long to hold tight♪

697
00:36:43,380 --> 00:36:47,740
♪To the loneliness in your hands♪

698
00:36:47,740 --> 00:36:50,740
♪Yet you warn me♪

699
00:36:50,740 --> 00:36:54,780
♪Any closer and I'll be set in stone♪

700
00:36:54,780 --> 00:36:56,380
♪The sunset deep in your heart♪

701
00:36:56,380 --> 00:37:04,260
♪Of the day you most loved me♪
